<def f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/widgets/qplaintextedit.cpp' l='2762' ll='2766' type='QPlainTextEdit::LineWrapMode QPlainTextEdit::lineWrapMode() const'/>
<doc f='qtbase-6.5.0/src/widgets/widgets/qplaintextedit.cpp' l='2752'>/*!
    \property QPlainTextEdit::lineWrapMode
    \brief the line wrap mode

    The default mode is WidgetWidth which causes words to be
    wrapped at the right edge of the text edit. Wrapping occurs at
    whitespace, keeping whole words intact. If you want wrapping to
    occur within words use setWordWrapMode().
*/</doc>
